'''''Pigskin''''' is a 1979 video game by Acorn Software Products for the [[TRS-80]] Model I Level II.

==Plot summary==
''Pigskin'' is a [[American football|football]] game with ten offensive plays and six defensive plays, and a player can either play against the computer opponent or another human opponent.<ref name="SG"/> In single-player mode there are five levels of difficulty.<ref name=pc1280/>

==Reception==
J. Mishcon reviewed ''Pigskin'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 30.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Mishcon|first=J. |date=August 1980 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=30|pages=29}}</ref> Mishcon commented that "A super game for kids who will love plenty of scoring but probably not the answer for a real lover of football."<ref name="SG"/>

